CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. A16 reads: "Victory Charity Club Contestants - These two charmers are Mrs. Constantine Smith, left, of Bethel AME Church, and Mrs. Juanita Baker of Ebenezer Baptist. They are contestants in annual affair given by the terrific Victory Charity Club, and will receive this honors at the tea, June 1, at the Centre Avenue YMCA.  Mrs. Hattie Matthews is general chairman; Miss Martha Tyson is program chairman.  Mrs. Viola Sams is president of this progressive club. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Victory Charity Club contestants Constantine Smith and Juanita Baker, standing in interior in front of light colored wall with dark marble wainscoting
